[test discarded]
# gen201: structural DISCARDED-RESULT localization — a second general bug smell
# (after gen200's symmetry break), judged by the real test suite. On the REAL
# astropy fitsrec.py (SWE-bench astropy-6938), parrot0 finds — from structure
# alone — a bare `output_field.replace(...)` whose value is thrown away (replace is
# a pure, value-returning method), and proposes assigning it back in place (the
# receiver is a parameter, so rebinding would be a no-op). Names nothing in
# advance. The real oracle (make swe-solve INSTANCE=astropy__astropy-6938) judges
# it RESOLVED; this hermetic case ratchets the derivation against regression.
> find the bug in tests/swebench/lite/astropy__astropy-6938/repo_excerpt/astropy/io/fits/fitsrec.py
< In tests/swebench/lite/astropy__astropy-6938/repo_excerpt/astropy/io/fits/fitsrec.py, `output_field.replace(encode_ascii('E'), encode_ascii('D'))` discards the result of a value-returning call; the fix is `output_field[:] = output_field.replace(encode_ascii('E'), encode_ascii('D'))`.

